post_text: Southern Reynolds County R-II was informed today by the Reynolds County Health Department that we have our first positive case of COVID-19 within the district. We are currently working in conjunction with the Health Department on contact tracing those who could be affected. The district is also thoroughly sanitizing the areas involved with the case as well as continuing our efforts throughout the campus. Our students health and safety remains our top priority. We appreciate your patience, understanding and continued support as we strive to provide our children a safe and high quality education.

post_text:
Registration Information:

Registration Days ‚Äì
Registration will take place in the FEMA gym this year.
One parent/guardian per household will enter the building using the new entrance where buses are unloaded into the commons area.
To ensure social distancing, the parent/guardian will complete registration systematically throughout the FEMA building at various stations.
It will not be necessary for students to attend registration.
Any student requiring help with their schedule, will need to contact Mr. Bouma to set up an appointment prior to Aug. 12th.
Any student enrolled in a dual credit class needs to monitor their email for communication from Mr. Bouma or Three Rivers College. Dual credit classes begin on Monday, August 17th.
We will try to complete this process in a timely manner and appreciate everyone‚Äôs cooperation and patience.

Registration Dates ‚Äì
Wednesday, August 12th: Last names A-G
Thursday, August 13th: Last names H-O
Friday, August 14th: Last names P-Z

from 9 am to 3 pm each day

* There will be no Open House for the 2020-2021 School Year

People‚Äôs Community Bank sponsored Student of the Month - May

Junior, Desiree Vest, is the daughter of Greg Vest and Donna Priest. She is a Varsity Cheerleader and a member of the Poetry Club. Her future plans include going to college to become a Forensic Scientist.

Junior, Chris Kuntz, is the son of Jimmie Kuntz and Raquel Kuntz and is a member of the BETA Club and FCA. Chris is employed at The 4-Way. Chris enjoys hunting and fishing in his spare time. He plans to attend college after high school.

People‚Äôs Community Bank will award each student with a $25 dollar Visa Card.

post_text:
People's Community Bank sponsored Students of the Month - April

Sophomore, Grace Lloyd, is the daughter of Matt and Amanda Lloyd. Grace is a member of the Varsity Cross Country Team, Volleyball Team, the bookkeeper for the Boys Basketball Team, BETA Club, FBLA, FCA, and her Church Youth Group. Grace would like to be a Veterinarian in her future.

Junior, Brycen King, is the son of Korey and Paula King. Brycen is a member of the Varsity Basketball and Baseball Teams, He is also a member of the BETA Club, FBLA, Quiz Bowl, FCA, Student Council, and Pep Club. His future plans include attending Missouri S & T and getting a degree in Mining Engineering.

Each student will get a $25 dollar Visa Card from People¬¥s Community Bank.

Guys, it's Shakespeare's birthday! I'm very sad that we don't get to celebrate together, but that won't stop the party bard from having a good time. Today is Shakespeare's estimated birthday (as the first and only documentation of his birth is his baptism on April 26, 1564) and also his death day seeing as he died on April 23, 1616. Cheers to 456 years!
Also, big shout out to our seniors being honored these next few days. I know that this is a tough time for you as you're missing out on your senior year. Just know that we miss you, love you, and support you during this time. Once a Whippet, always a Whippet! üß°
-Ms. Midkiff and William Shakespeare

After consulting with State and local health officials, as well as President Trump‚Äôs Executive Order on social distancing,the Southern Reynolds County R-II School District is extending the COVID-19 Health and Wellness closure through Thursday, April 30.During this time, all school events are postponed. The administration is currently looking at possible dates for Prom and Graduation to be rescheduled. As circumstances continue to fluctuate, it is difficult to predict what this situation will be a month from now. But, we will be working to find solutions to our challenges ahead!
We will continue to serve meals on Mondays and Wednesdays during the extended closure. Make sure you continue to sign up for meals on the District‚Äôs homepage.
Please know that we will continue to update and modify our plans and will share them as we move forward. Thank you for your patience and support during this challenging time for our students and staff!

post_text:
The Three Rivers College Athletic Hall of Fame inducted its first four inductees with a banquet on January 31, 2020.

A big Whippet shout out to our very own Paula Corder-King for being inducted into the Three Rivers College Hall of Fame.

"The first Lady Raiders basketball player to have her number retired, Paula Corder-King had a storied career at Three Rivers during the 1996-97 and 1997-98 seasons. She was a two-time NJCAA All American, named 2nd Team All American her freshman year and 1st Team All American as a sophomore. Corder-King was also named All Region 16 and All MCCAC Conference both of her seasons at TRC. She is the All Time Leading Scorer for the Three Rivers Lady Raiders basketball team and best Free Throw Shooter in Lady Raiders basketball history."-darnews.com

Senior Caleb is the son of Rick and Nicole. Caleb is a member of the Varsity Whippet Basketball Team. He enjoys hanging out with his friends in his spare time. His future plans are to go to a carpentry school in St. Louis.

post_text: Middle School Student Council is hosting a dance for Ellington 6th-8th graders on November 8, 2019 from 6:00-8:30 pm. The theme of the dance is "Glow Up 2019!" Students are encouraged to wear white or neon casual clothing that adheres to the school dress code. The dance will be held in the Multipurpose Room and there is a $2 admission fee. Snacks and drinks will be provided at no cost to the students.
